text: Jindřich Blažek (26 November 1933 – 1997) was a Czech rower who represented Czechoslovakia. He competed at the 1960 Summer Olympics in Rome with the men's coxless four where they came fourth. ==References== Category:1933 births Category:1997 deaths Category:Czechoslovak male rowers Category:Olympic rowers of Czechoslovakia Category:Rowers at the 1960 Summer Olympics Category:Rowers from Prague Category:European Rowing Championships medalists
